Bootstrap: docker
From: python:3.12-slim

%labels
    Author jlanej
    Description UCR hg38-to-T2T-CHM13 liftover pipeline

%files
    convert_ucr_to_t2t.py /app/convert_ucr_to_t2t.py
    validate_liftover.py /app/validate_liftover.py
    compute_unique_fraction.py /app/compute_unique_fraction.py
    requirements.txt /app/requirements.txt
    resources /app/resources

%post
    apt-get update && \
        apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends ca-certificates wget libcurl4 && \
        rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
    pip install --no-cache-dir -r /app/requirements.txt
    # Bake the UCSC binaries into the image (small tools, ~3 MB each)
    wget --tries=3 --waitretry=5 -O /app/liftOver \
        "https://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/exe/linux.x86_64/liftOver" && \
    wget --tries=3 --waitretry=5 -O /app/bigBedToBed \
        "https://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/exe/linux.x86_64/bigBedToBed" && \
    wget --tries=3 --waitretry=5 -O /app/twoBitToFa \
        "https://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/exe/linux.x86_64/twoBitToFa" && \
    wget --tries=3 --waitretry=5 -O /app/bigBedInfo \
        "https://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/exe/linux.x86_64/bigBedInfo" && \
    # Keep bigBedSummary available for UCSC mappability track sanity checks.
    wget --tries=3 --waitretry=5 -O /app/bigBedSummary \
        "https://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/admin/exe/linux.x86_64/bigBedSummary" && \
        chmod +x /app/liftOver /app/bigBedToBed /app/twoBitToFa /app/bigBedInfo /app/bigBedSummary

%environment
    export OUTPUT_DIR="${OUTPUT_DIR:-$(pwd)}"

%runscript
    exec python /app/convert_ucr_to_t2t.py "$@"

%help
    Lift over human Ultraconserved Regions from hg38 to T2T-CHM13v2.0.
    The liftOver, bigBedToBed, twoBitToFa, bigBedInfo, and bigBedSummary binaries are bundled in the image.
    Large data files (ultras bigBed when missing, chain file, genomes) are downloaded
    automatically on first run.

    One-liner (pulls image, runs pipeline, writes output to CWD):
        apptainer run --bind "$(pwd):/output" docker://ghcr.io/jlanej/ultra_conserved_region_research:latest

    Or build a local SIF from this definition file:
        apptainer build ucr-liftover.sif Apptainer.def
        apptainer run ucr-liftover.sif

    Validate liftover with sequence alignment:
        apptainer exec --bind "$(pwd):/output" ucr-liftover.sif python /app/validate_liftover.py

    Compute strict k=24 unique-genome fraction:
        apptainer exec --bind "$(pwd):/output" ucr-liftover.sif python /app/compute_unique_fraction.py

    Output files (liftover):
        ucr_hg38.bed            - input UCR coordinates (hg38)
        ucr_t2t_chm13.bed       - mapped coordinates (T2T-CHM13)
        ucr_unmapped.bed        - unmapped regions with reasons
        ucr_liftover_audit.tsv  - full audit report for QC

    Output files (validation):
        ucr_sequences_hg38.fa       - extracted hg38 UCR sequences
        ucr_sequences_t2t.fa        - extracted T2T-CHM13 UCR sequences
        ucr_alignment_report.tsv    - per-region alignment statistics
        ucr_alignment_details.txt   - visual alignments for divergent pairs

    Override output directory:
        OUTPUT_DIR=/scratch/proj apptainer run ucr-liftover.sif
